```
@Autowired
private Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder jsonBuilder;

...

@Bean
public ISEAClient createPubClient() {
    OkHttpClient client = new OkHttpClient();   
    return new HttpRestSEAClient(&quot;http://localhost:8081/sea/&quot;, client, jsonBuilder.build());
}
```

A `@Bean` method in a `@Configuration` class can have other beans injected as arguments. Instead of explicitly getting the bean from context, do this:

```
@Configuration
public class ClientConfig {

  @Bean
  public ISEAClient createPubClient(ObjectMapper objectMapper) {
    OkHttpClient client = new OkHttpClient();   
    return new HttpRestSEAClient(&quot;http://localhost:8081/sea/&quot;, client, objectMapper);
  }

}
```

Or to get a unique `ObjectMapper` as @JosephGalea suggested, do this: 

```
@Configuration
public class ClientConfig {

  @Bean
  public ISEAClient createPubClient(Jackson2ObjectMapperBuilder builder) {
    OkHttpClient client = new OkHttpClient();   
    return new HttpRestSEAClient(&quot;http://localhost:8081/sea/&quot;, client, builder.build());
  }

}
```

