Here is the Java tutorial on processing _I/O data_ using either of those frameworks.  
_[Lesson: Basic I/O (The Java&amp;trade; Tutorials &amp;gt; Essential Java Classes)](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/io/index.html)_

The _java.io_ framework is good for basic file reading and writing.  
Whereas, the _java.nio_ framework can prove daunting on general purpose access.

Essentially, the _java.nio_ framework encapsulates the _[InputStream](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/io/InputStream.html)_ and _[OutputStream](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/io/OutputStream.html)_ classes of the original _java.io_, in order to provide a more robust application in scalable and multi-tiered designs.  

