Here&#39;s what I can tell you on this... There are good libraries out there that can simplify this process for you.

Since you are using spring I would start off by grabbing the dependecy listed here:
https://github.com/graphql-java-kickstart/graphql-spring-boot
Source docs: https://www.graphql-java-kickstart.com/spring-boot/getting-started/

Using this dependency offers ease of consumption as you can set the query to be in a more readable format by placing your queries in the resources folder like

query.graphql

From there

You can create a model object containing all of the values you are expecting to be returned by your graphql response. I would just make a pojo class using:  https://www.jsonschema2pojo.org/

Then to consume here is an example:

       // If no other function is calling then remove the docID param. Could be used to enable specific searching
    public Example graphQl(String docID){
        
        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();
        WebClient webClient = WebClient.builder()
                .baseUrl(&quot;TheEndpointURI&quot;)
                .defaultHeader(&quot;apikey&quot;, &quot;apikey value&quot;)
                .build();
        
        Map&lt;String,Object&gt; vars = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
        vars.put(&quot;docId&quot;, docID); // remove if not using docID
        vars.put(&quot;filter&quot;, &quot;anyFilters you might want?&quot; );
        
        GraphQLWebClient graphQLWebClient = GraphQLWebClient.newInstance(webClient, objectMapper);
        
        Example example = null;
        
        try{
            
            example = graphQLWebClient.post(&quot;query.graphql&quot;, vars, Example.class).cblock();
            
        } catch (Exception e){
            log.error(e.getMessage());
        }
        return example;
    }

Example query.graphql

        query bookDetails {
      bookById(id: &quot;book-1&quot;){
        id
        name
        pageCount
        author {
          firstName
          lastName
        }
      }
    }

