answers.body_markdown:
Given `String s`,

    s = s.replace(&quot;\\&quot;, &quot;\\\\&quot;);

Replaces all `\` with `\\`.

You should use the [`StringEscapeUtils`][1] class from [Apache Commons Text][2] (you can also find the class in Apache Commons Lang3 but that one is deprecated).  You&#39;ll find that there are plenty of other offerings in Apache Commons that might serve useful for other problems you have in Java development, so that you don&#39;t reinvent the wheel.

The specific call you want has to do with &quot;Java escaping&quot;; the API call is [`StringEscapeUtils.escapeJava()`][3]. For example:

    System.out.println(StringEscapeUtils.escapeJava(&quot;Hello\r\n\tW\&quot;o\&quot;rld\n&quot;));

would print out:

    Hello\r\n\tW\&quot;o\&quot;rld\n


There are plenty of other escaping utilities in that library as well. You can find [Apache Commons Text in Maven Central][4] and you&#39;d add it to your Maven project like this:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.commons&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;commons-text&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;1.3&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

and in case you are using Gradle:

    compile &quot;org.apache.commons:commons-text:1.3&quot;


  [1]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-text/javadocs/api-release/org/apache/commons/text/StringEscapeUtils.html
  [2]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-text/
  [3]: https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-text/javadocs/api-release/org/apache/commons/text/StringEscapeUtils.html#escapeJava-java.lang.String-
  [4]: https://search.maven.org/#search%7Cgav%7C1%7Cg%3A%22org.apache.commons%22%20AND%20a%3A%22commons-text%22

I had the same issue, the problem was in the @ContextConfiguration in me test classes, i was loading the servlet context too i just change:

    @ContextConfiguration(locations = { &quot;classpath*:**\*-context.xml&quot;, &quot;classpath*:**\*-config.xml&quot; })

to:

    @ContextConfiguration(locations = { &quot;classpath:**\*-context.xml&quot;, &quot;classpath:**\*-config.xml&quot; })

and that&#180;s it.
this way im only loading all the files with the pattern *-context.xml in me test path.

